{"id":10210,"date":"2018-11-11T17:33:50","date_gmt":"2018-11-12T01:33:50","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/?p=10210"},"modified":"2024-07-21T16:16:45","modified_gmt":"2024-07-21T23:16:45","slug":"deutscher-soldtenfrienhof-vladslo-belgium","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2018\/11\/11\/deutscher-soldtenfrienhof-vladslo-belgium\/","title":{"rendered":"DEUTSCHER SOLDTENFRIENHOF, Vladslo Belgium"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">The Flanders area of Western Wallonian is full of WWII war cemeteries. The Allied cemeteries are common and full of visitors but I was the only person as this German one.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">After the war, there were 678 German military cemeteries with 134,000 soldiers in Belgium alone. In 1925, the number was reduced to 128 and in 1954 to just four: Hooglede (8,247), Langemark (44,294 including 25,000 in a mass grave), Menen (47,864), and Vladslo (25,645). Initially, there were wooden blocks with a bronze plaque that were replaced by the current granite grave markers each commemorating 20 soldiers.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"irc_mil i3597\" tabindex=\"0\" href=\"https:\/\/foursquare.com\/v\/deutscher-soldatenfriedhof-vladslo\/4f68470fe4b05eede4ea056a\/photos\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-noload=\"\" data-ved=\"2ahUKEwij9emR2s3eAhV0HTQIHaK4DWEQjRx6BAgBEAU\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"irc_mi\" src=\"https:\/\/igx.4sqi.net\/img\/general\/600x600\/37613442_m2mupqEuiB9PH6xLXz2H7gfC0mq0os0F6ZZ4yzfcMy8.jpg\" alt=\"Image result for DEUTSCHER SOLDATENFRIEDHOF, Vladslo Belgium\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" \/><\/a><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Vladslo, amid oak trees, is best known for the two statues\u00a0<em>Grieving Parents<\/em>\u00a0created by Kathie Kollwitze whose son Peter is buried at the foot of the father\u2019s statue. They are universal symbols for every parent who has lost a child to the tragedy of war and are renowned for their simplicity: the father is kneeling with hunched shoulders but his head is erect and the mother is kneeling but head bowed. Both have their arms crossed in front.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"irc_mil i3597\" tabindex=\"0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.gettyimages.co.uk\/detail\/news-photo\/k%C3%A4the-kollwitz-lost-her-youngest-son-peter-on-the-news-photo\/167017681\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-noload=\"\" data-ved=\"2ahUKEwju-aHT2c3eAhUgIjQIHewaB60QjRx6BAgBEAU\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"irc_mi\" src=\"https:\/\/media.gettyimages.com\/photos\/kthe-kollwitz-lost-her-youngest-son-peter-on-the-battlefield-in-world-picture-id167017681?k=6&amp;m=167017681&amp;s=612x612&amp;w=0&amp;h=CkLGNPc0zgIICKTHFtGw60mFDoUod_QlkWCPofFhdC4=\" alt=\"Image result for DEUTSCHER SOLDATENFRIEDHOF, Vladslo Belgium\" width=\"622\" height=\"413\" \/><\/a><\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">When I was here, in contrast to the Allied cemeteries, there were no other visitors.<\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The Flanders area of Western Wallonian is full of WWII war cemeteries. The Allied cemeteries are common and full of visitors but I was the only person as this German one. After the war, there were 678 German military cemeteries &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2018\/11\/11\/deutscher-soldtenfrienhof-vladslo-belgium\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta